data.name: Darture (TEST, DELETE BEFORE BRANCHING)
data.joke: The ball has begun. I look forward to your performance, sir.
data.description: Putting on the perfect smile is a basic skill for a lady, as are elegant dance steps and flexible tactics.

data.name: Vepley
data.joke: Is there a new show coming up? Vepley is su~per ex~ci~ted☆!
data.description: An idol who shines on the unique stage, the "battlefield"! She prepares meticulously every day for her next performance—this way, she will not easily trip or bump into others again.

data.name: Angriper
data.joke: "Do not lump me in with those sorry pieces of fodder!"
data.description: They're proud of being superior to others in the Varjager chain of command, but all too often, they end up meeting the same fate as the other Felagi.

data.name: Darture
data.joke: The ball has begun. I look forward to your performance, sir.
data.description: Putting on the perfect smile is a basic skill for a lady, as are elegant dance steps and flexible tactics.

data.name: Aegis Bulwark Type I
data.joke: If an Aegis Deadeye attacks an Aegis Bulwark, who would win?
data.description: Sangvis Ferri Manufacturing does it again! Sturdy, reliable, and without those flashy and impractical Doll bodies. Load up on armor plate to double your defense at half the price!

data.name: Gere
data.joke: There's no such thing as a free lunch, but the Varjagers are always angling for one.
data.description: A gigantic mech loaded with booty, said to come from a Varjager joke.

data.name: Deserter 07
data.joke: Let's go out with a bang.
data.description: There's no future in staying with the Varjagers—upon realizing this, certain "geniuses" ran as fast as their feet could take them.

data.name: Deserter 03
data.joke: Just a silent coolie.
data.description: There's no future in staying with the Varjagers—upon realizing this, certain "geniuses" ran as fast as their feet could take them.

data.name: Felade Type I
data.joke: Fire enough rounds and you're bound to hit eventually.
data.description: What on earth could have transformed them from human beings into apes, charging blindly at others on the battlefield?

data.name: Crysmole Type I
data.joke: You attack it, it attacks you. You attack something else and it STILL attacks you.
data.description: A blind and unreasonable mole that's been piling on the creatine. It's ill-natured and its gigantic body means they're always hungry.

data.name: Ravn
data.joke: "Destroy anything you can't take, don't leave anything behind!"
data.description: Every component of the Ravn appears to originate from different pieces of engineering machinery, all personally "acquired" by Berserl. The machine gun, main cannon, and massive hammer are all formidable weapons in their own right.

data.name: Aegis SWAP Bulwark
data.joke: Full of security, full of love.
data.description: An upgraded version of the Aegis. Its improvements are focused on its defensive systems, making it tougher and more durable, like what one would expect of the name "Bulwark".

data.name: Target Drone - Giordre
data.joke: Tactical pause.
data.description: It won't launch attacks on you, but who's to say glaring at people isn't a form of attack?

data.name: Felaste
data.joke: Just chuck it out there, we'll see if it lands.
data.description: The simplicity of their molotovs has surely demonstrated their frenzy. Naturally, if they can't make enough molotovs in time, handguns would also suffice.

data.name: Krolik
data.description: She has a bit of a temper and shows little interest in matters unrelated to herself, but her sense of responsibility is beyond reproach. Even if she is assigned a mission she absolutely detests, such as "serving as Nemesis' exclusive translator", she will still give it her all.

data.name: Nemesis
data.description: Passionate in mysticism and divination, she always carries a magical divination tool known as the "Prism". Her divination results are often expressed in a cryptic and enigmatic manner. Though she can be difficult to communicate with, she remains a dependable companion.

data.name: Colphne
data.description: Everything we have sacrificed is for the sake of that final outcome. So keep going like this... smile, and carry on.

data.name: Vepley
data.description: An idol who shines on the unique stage, the "battlefield"! She prepares meticulously every day for her next performance—this way, she will not easily trip or bump into others again.

data.name: Groza
data.description: Getting a group of Dolls with unique personalities to complete their various missions has always been a topic of consideration for Groza. First, she needs to understand the abilities of each team member, then make a sensible plan that takes them all into account — While things haven't always gone as planned, everyone is still reasonably cohesive.

data.name: Peritya
data.description: Fighting, survival and all manner of new emotions are all part of this vast world. This place is full of interesting mystery, unlike the electronic world... Hm, that cloud finally blocked out the sun, time to lie down for a rest.

data.name: Lenna
data.description: A cheerful and friendly Doll who goes to great lengths to protect her cherished family. Over time, she has become more composed and developed a perfect smile when interacting with others. She also "forcibly" gives her family heartfelt hugs whenever she sees them.

data.name: Dushevnaya
data.description: Temporarily filled, character sheet must be synchronized later

data.name: Sharkry
data.description: A mischievous, impish Doll whose sweet smiles hide a cute cunning. She is hungry not only for the stage but also for the boundless adoration from her customers. ♥

data.name: Cheeta
data.description: This Doll with a ceaseless fountain of inspiration is Griffin's Queen of Inventions. Undeterred by countless setbacks, her mind churns out a whirlwind of quirky, headache-inducing ideas. Yet, when the moment demands it, she always manages to come up with ingenious solutions.

data.name: Tololo
data.description: A serene Doll who finds solace under the starry sky. Hidden beneath her reticence is a delicate and sensitive soul. When the world slumbers, she confides in the vast cosmos and delights in the stars that seem to shine just for her.

data.name: Nagant
data.description: A Doll who likes to play the mature grown-up but looks up to heroes and also aspires to be one. Even after leaving the battlefield, she continues to shine as a security Doll, ensuring peaceful nights.

data.name: Qiongjiu
data.description: A Doll who limits her personal freedom in order to shoulder her team's heavy responsibilities. She dedicates her time and energy to Griffin, but is capable of maintaining her individuality thanks to her precise and efficient work planning. She never deviates, and never breaks the rules; rather than changing the plan, she prefers to change reality and herself.

data.name: Centaureissi
data.description: A humble yet principled Doll. She brews aromatic coffee and stands as the steadfast guardian of the café—she is the irreplaceable shield of "Zucchero".

data.name: Sabrina
data.description: A Doll passionate about culinary research and enjoying food, the kitchen is her new battlefield. Loves sharing her cooking process, though aroma may have boundaries, her smile spreads through the network, infecting every viewer.

data.name: Daiyan
data.description: A gentle and reserved Doll who roams the lands with both her guzheng and her bandmates from "Monsoon". When she plucks the strings, she masterfully evokes her listeners' deepest desires—listening to all, embracing all.

data.name: Jiangyu
data.description: A lively and enthusiastic Doll who follows in her older sister's footsteps with a carefree spirit. She roams the lands with her bandmates, bringing fresh and fiery notes to "Monsoon".

data.name: Littara
data.description: An extremely introverted doll who needs to communicate through writing. She is meticulous and thorough, playing a "strategist" role in the team. After switching to a new Imprint Model, she has become even more reliable, supporting her teammates' dreams daily.

data.name: Mosin-Nagant
data.description: A Doll who loves to help others and strives to improve her negative mindset. Her motto is to never avoid challenges; once motivated, she gives her all. While negative thoughts may linger in her neural cloud, her radiant smile and enthusiastic actions surely inspire many of her companions.

data.name: Ksenia
data.description: A Doll with an unusual obsession with making money, she finds a sense of security by working hard to earn it and then spending it all. However, the time she spends working with her reliable companions is equally her treasure.

data.name: Follower Goliath
data.joke: Look out! There's a bomb!
data.description: A Goliath carried by the Deichgraf, it wipes out all enemies with its explosion. As a follower, it faithfully defends the fortress behind it.

data.name: Felaskju Type III
data.joke: Of COURSE it hurts!—crucial feedback from a hit teammate.
data.description: Their weapons might not be fancy or anything, but they've got cunning in spades. Be careful when passing by shaded areas; you might run into a Varjager sniper taking aim.

data.name: Makiatto
data.description: A calm, proud, yet awkward Doll who isn't good at expressing herself. She loves fluffy little animals and overly sweet macchiatos. Always a loner, her gaze often lingers somewhere. When will she finally get the response she's been longing for?

data.name: Ullrid
data.description: A Doll with great ambitions. She draws friends to her side with her bold nature and strong decisiveness. However, she occasionally longs for a quiet corner to unload her burden and rest.

data.name: Lotta
data.description: This Doll, who is both exceedingly shy and cautious, has a knack for noticing subtle details that others miss. Do keep in mind that her slow and reserved nature when socializing may require some extra patience and understanding.

data.name: Angriper
data.joke: "Do not lump me in with those sorry pieces of fodder!"
data.description: They're proud of being superior to others in the Varjager chain of command, but all too often, they end up meeting the same fate as the other Felagi.

data.name: Giordre
data.joke: Standing at the rear is also part of the strategy.
data.description: Although they're often mocked for hiding behind the rest of the team and telling them what to do, it has to be said that you need to survive to become a Giordre.

data.name: Overfaller
data.joke: Very useful. —A Giordre's opinion.
data.description: A big brainless lunk wielding a giant bludgeon. It obeys the Giordres, because the ones who can think for themselves, even a little bit, all end up dying in strange places.

data.name: Urokrake
data.joke: Doesn't matter if you use your guns or trashtalk; anything goes as long as it trips up the opposition.
data.description: Varjager members operating "cutting edge" weaponry are usually heavily guarded. However, should their weapons be lost, the "Urokrake" will immediately replace them.

data.name: Tosk
data.joke: Imitation is the highest form of flattery; which makes this an utter sycophant.
data.description: This mech is a crude copy of Ravn. It's missing parts here and there, but its clumsy movements are on point. Its performance is pretty much the same as the original, but its firepower is a little bit on the low side.

data.name: Tosk

data.description: This mech is a crude copy of Ravn. It's missing parts here and there, but its clumsy movements are on point. Its performance is pretty much the same as the original, but its firepower is a little bit on the low side.

data.name: Ironside
data.joke: It's probably just a teensy bit more complicated than piloting a remote-controlled car... probably.
data.description: A semi-autonomous, multifunctional combat android "kindly" appropriated by a Varjager member. Equipped with remote control capabilities, its combat power is largely determined by the operator's skill level.

data.name: Oljefat
data.joke: Losing 800 of their own to take out a thousand enemies? They wouldn't even bat an eye.
data.description: The Oljefats revel in the thrill of destruction. They are deeply feared, even within the Varjagers. The voracious flames bring them a twisted euphoria, as if they hold dominion over all.

data.name: Mishap Thorn
data.joke: You can't deal with this one like you would a normal bear, so just run.
data.description: It's a Thorn that's even more savage and spiky than a normal Thorn. By the way, the thorns adorning it are not cute little pine needles like you might see on a Christmas tree. If you see it, run as fast as you can.

data.name: Sneaker Crysmole
data.joke: “Hey, why's the soil so loose?!”
data.description: These Crysmoles have relearned how to dig pits to set traps and have constantly topped the "Most Hated ELID" lists in the Yellow Zones for a while now. It has ruined countless places with its digging, putting the icing on the cake of desolation that is the Yellow Zone.

data.name: Atrocity Thorn
data.joke: If your hands became like that, even if you could crack an acorn's shell, you wouldn't be able to eat it, right?
data.description: A Thorn whose forelimbs are more mutated than others of its kind. Its thorns are also harder and crystallized, giving it more lethality when making close range attacks.

data.name: Lycosa Singoriensis
data.joke: The arachnophobe's greatest nightmare.
data.description: These spine-chilling predators always come in packs. In their lairs, every webbed cocoon is a lost soul with unfinished business.

data.name: Nemertea
data.joke: How on earth are these parts stitched together?
data.description: Extensible tendrils, viscous fluids, and an enormous body—this "composite" entity defies conventional understanding.

data.name: Scourge Moth
data.joke: Its appearance drives the ELIDs into a frenzy.
data.description: Large moths with eerie patterns on their bodies. Their massive size prevents free flight, but each flap of the wings disperses scales far more toxic than any other moth can muster.

data.name: Nemertea
data.joke: How on earth are these parts stitched together?
data.description: Extensible tendrils, viscous fluids, and an enormous body—this "composite" entity defies conventional understanding.

data.name: Nemertea
data.joke: How on earth are these parts stitched together?
data.description: Extensible tendrils, viscous fluids, and an enormous body—this "composite" entity defies conventional understanding.

data.name: Sewage Skipper
data.joke: The flutter of a butterfly's wing can cause a devastating chain of events.
data.description: A large butterfly that relies on its massive abdominal cavity to float. It has an altered digestive system within its abdomen that allows it to secrete a black, corrosive fluid. When this fluid mixes with water before discharge, it transforms into a black mist permeated with an ominous aura.

data.name: Nemertea
data.joke: How on earth are these parts stitched together?

data.name: Nemertea - Mutant
data.joke: A familiar nightmare, but more terrifying and oppressive.
data.description: It's the same old "stitched-together creature" that defies the imagination, but it's strangely different in some way?

data.name: Nemertea - Mutant

data.name: Temblor Titan
data.joke: Feel the music of our muzzles!
data.description: A fearsome weapon equipped with numerous ways of unleashing firepower. Its synchronized sonic emitter allows for a potent secondary attack on adversaries.

data.name: Terrorhorn Chimera
data.joke: No feeding. Beware its spit, which can spew forth at any moment.
data.description: A Boojum created via repeating fusing of specimens. Tremendous in size and covered in durable scales, and a wide field of vision allows it to be very perceptive. Its mighty forelimbs can attack at close range, and it spews its poisonous spit in all directions. Whether up close or at range, this beast is thoroughly difficult to fend off.

data.name: Aegis SWAP Artillery
data.joke: Start at range, seize the day!
data.description: An upgraded version of the Aegis, essentially a mobile turret that prides itself on its cyclic rate and high firepower, ensuring victory for you and your team from the starting line.

data.name: Aegis SWAP Claymore
data.joke: Beware electric hazards!
data.description: Is that the sound of a keen blade whooshing through the air, or the crackling of an electric current? Neither of them seem pleasant.

data.name: Scout SWAP
data.joke: It shakes its head back and forth and jumps back and forth. Does it have a mind of its own?
data.description: An improved model from Sangvis Ferri manufacturing! Compared to the older model, it's got better output, and more nimble movements, making it great for aerial support.

data.name: Aegis SWAP Bulwark
data.joke: Full of security, full of love.
data.description: An upgraded version of the Aegis. Its improvements are focused on its defensive systems, making it tougher and more durable, like what one would expect of the name "Bulwark".

data.name: Aegis SWAP Myrmidon
data.joke: The Aegis Myrmidon, providing you with a professional and versatile solution to the enemy.
data.description: An upgraded version of the Aegis. It now focuses on variable attack methods, allowing it to choose from the best option to suit the field conditions. Ever-changing and dynamic, so just take your pick.

data.name: Darture
data.joke: Your punishment has only just begun, sir.
data.description: The tip of the lady's umbrella is wreathed in lethal sparks. When the fire rises, it makes the battlefield even more beautiful.

data.name: Aegis SWAP Dominator
data.joke: After fighting, they can also come together to play poker.
data.description: One of the upgraded versions of the Aegis series, equipped with several Centralized Goliaths. Gain the powerful combination of Aegis and Goliath with just one small additional payment. Order now!

data.name: Flareberus
data.joke: A Super Dinergate among Super Dinergates.
data.description: A large machine modified by the wanted criminal Peterke Farkas. It was originally a Super Dinergate. Its "badass" looks come from Farkas' sense of aesthetics.

data.name: Flareberus
data.joke: A Super Dinergate among Super Dinergates.

data.name: Niter No.249
data.joke: Her voice is kindly enough, but she isn't necessarily a friend.
data.description: A cute girl who's always smiling and full of warmth. No matter how the battlefield changes, her gentle kindness will always stay the same.

data.name: Custos 052
data.joke: In any group, he's always the one with the worst luck when it comes to people.
data.description: For him, death is a small price to pay if he can eliminate his enemies. This makes him extremely destructive.

data.name: Custos 036
data.joke: He spreads his arms to embrace the sun.
data.description: For him, obeying orders is his only principle.

data.name: Bellator 137
data.joke: Skilled in team battles, his only partner is Bellator-212.
data.description: Coarse of hide, solid of frame, his body is corpulent yet strong. The girthiest warrior of them all.

data.name: Bellator 212
data.joke: When it comes to independent thinking, he's on the same level as Bellator-137.
data.description: Just like Bellator-137, he had a mighty body, but it didn't keep him safe; instead, it only accelerated his demise.

data.name: Production Expert
data.joke: Be not fooled by her demeanor, for she holds a whip in her hands.
data.description: A unique defense mechanism with a specified jurisdiction, fashioned with the capability to issue commands to lower-ranked defense mechanisms through the use of electronic cards. It also possesses significant combat capabilities of its own.

data.name: Creepy Doll
data.joke: Rationality manifest, completely devoid of emotion.
data.description: A specter wandering through desolate ruins, seemingly guarding, awaiting, and resisting something simultaneously.

data.name: Data Remains SWAP
data.joke: The target is to dominate Level II.
data.description: Materialized data shards within Level II have superior combat performance compared to ordinary Data Remains and more potent attack methods.

data.name: Scout Vanguard
data.joke: The finest tour guide in the Contaminated Zone. Don't mind it occasionally consuming a guest.
data.description: A human officer of the Scout Corps. Highly knowledgeable about the Contaminated Zone's topography due to long periods of deployment in scouting assignments, rectifying the downfalls created by outdated equipment. Resourceful and cautious, a geological expert any team would appreciate.

data.name: Strike Captain
data.joke: No one knew of his infiltration. No one alive, at least.
data.description: Becoming a core officer of Magni Security requires outstanding management and command abilities as well as personal prowess. A Strike Captain is an expert in combat at a variety of ranges and is highly adaptable in the field, posing a lethal threat to any enemy.

data.name: Mechanist
data.joke: Was fined on many occasions for walking a pet without a leash.
data.description: Operations in the field, whether combat or logistical in nature, rely upon mecha-hounds. The mechanists carry upon them many maintenance toolboxes for this reason.

data.name: Blaster
data.joke: Was fined on many occasions for setting off fireworks in violation of regulations.
data.description: Demolitionists carrying varieties of equipment and explosives. Provides key support fire or cover, as well as clearing out paths of attack.

data.name: Flyer
data.joke: Insecticide will do little to them, but it's not like you need to bring out the big guns.
data.description: The main body of a squad's firepower. Capable of flexibly traversing long distances on the battlefield via flight and delivering a fatal blow.

data.name: Blusphere
data.joke: She fights by her lonesome, cutting off her own body to gain allies.
data.description: A strange Doll of unknown origins, disfigured in appearance. Parts of her metal endoskeleton lay exposed, with massive burn marks and marring wounds beneath her almost translucent skin. In stark contrast with her striking appearance she displays an otherworldly calm, not a shred of emotion upon her steel-cold face.

data.name: Bellflea Type I

data.name: Terrorhorn Chimera
data.joke: No feeding. Beware its spit, which can spew forth at any moment.
data.description: A Boojum created via repeating fusing of specimens. Tremendous in size and covered in durable scales, and a wide field of vision allows it to be very perceptive. Its mighty forelimbs can attack at close range, and it spews its poisonous spit in all directions. Whether up close or at range, this beast is thoroughly difficult to fend off.

data.description: Formerly a hunter with trustworthy companions until he was confined by those companions due to mutations on his personage. No longer accepted in his tribe, he is forced to make company with the dregs of humanity, existing as the more rational of his band.
